div
  #blur_dark
  #caption(style='color: white; text-align: center; margin: 0;')
    h2(style='font-size: 40px; margin-bottom: 50px;') Planned Features
  div(style='color: white; text-align: justify; margin: 0; margin-left: 20%; margin-right: 20%; font-size: 20px;')
    p
      | The LogiJS project is in a state where many important features of a logic simulator are integrated but
      | we&apos;re
      | planning to implement a lot of new stuff to make LogiJS more powerful and easier to use. These are some
      | features
      | that we want to integrate in the future, in no specific order:
      ul
        li
          b Copying parts of a sketch:
          |  At the moment, LogiJS gives you the ability to select parts of
          |                         a sketch.
          |                         These parts can be dragged to another place or be deleted from the sketch. We want to extend
          |                         this features
          |                         to enable the user to copy parts of a sketch and paste it multiple times.
        br
        li
          b Support for the VHDL hardware description language:
          |  VHDL is a language to describe
          |                         logical circuits, like the one you can create in LogiJS, in a standardized form, for example to
          |                         execute them on an FPGA. Having an option to im- and export VHDL code may be an important
          |                         feature for the use of LogiJS in education.
        br
        li
          b Reorganize the components in the toolbox:
          |  The toolbox on the left side may be confusing
          |                         for beginners and some similar components could be accessed with just one button, for example
          |                         components that exist with various bit widths. Also, some basic components are missing and
          |                         should be added as standard components. It would be nice to have a selection of your own
          |                         components under the standard ones. This requires having individual user accounts.
        br
    p(style='text-align: center;')
      b Got ideas for upcoming features?
    p(style='text-align: center;')
      b
        | Just open an issue on 
        a(href='https://www.github.com/SimonBuxx/LogiJS') GitHub
